This 360 photo image (equirectangular panorama) taken on May 23, 2018 shows a general view of the Luzhniki Stadium in Moscow, ahead of the Russia 2018 World Cup football tournament. / AFP PHOTO / Mladen ANTONOV / The opening ceremony and the first match of the tournament will take place at Moscow’s Luzhniki Stadium, which has been specially constructed for the competition. The Luzhniki stadium will host 7 world cup matches including opening and final. It’s Russia’s biggest and national stadium hosted in a sports complex. Here are 12 facts about the venue and opening ceremony.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .